This paper deals with information theoretical secrecy and secret key generation, which are topics typically studied in the field of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses wire-tap channel models, which are commonly studied in the field of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of hash functions and entropy measures suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the fields of coding theory (cs.CC) and communication theory (cs.CE). Finally, the mention of public discussion for secret key distillation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of multimedia security (cs.MM).
